The paper deals with the construction of quantum error-correcting codes, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. However, based on the content of the abstract, the most likely sub-category is cs.IT (Information Theory), as the paper discusses the minimum distance of quantum codes and their ability to correct errors. The other likely sub-categories are cs.QI (Quantum Physics), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity), as these subfields are also relevant to quantum error-correcting codes.
